-->First Switch to Root User: sudo su -
-->git --version (To Verify the Version Of Git)
-->git config --list(Global Configuration from which commit will happen)
-->cd mumbaigit --> move to mumbaigit directory
-->mkdir mumbaigit
-->Inside the directory run--> git init
-->Once git init command is get executed three stages will get created i.e workspace,staging/index(invisible,imaginary),localrepo
-->local repo has one branch which is main branch.
-->One hidden file will get created which is .git file which is created in workspace and is called local repo
-->Create one file with the Name GitWorkFlowSumeet, To create a file vi GitWorkFlowSumeet
-->To verify run--> ls -a 
-->To verify the status of the file run --> git status
-->It will show untracked file because Git cannot track this file because the file is in workspace only.
-->To add the copy of the file to staging area run the below command
--> Git add . or Git add filename
--> . represents current directory if multiple files then use .
--> Now run git status command to verify
--> Git took the snapshot of the file including data inside it but haven't commited it yet
-->In order to save the snapshot permanently in local repo run the command
--> git commit -m "workflow commit" -m is a message which tells what comment u want to enter
--> run git status to verify
-->open the file with command cat GitWorkFlowSumeet see the data
-->run ls -a
-->git log -->This command will show the commit in local repository with commit id(latest will show first)
-->git show commitid(enter first 7 commit id)
